---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
	title="About Daniel"
	description="Learn about Daniel Thorp — his experience in student governance, campus leadership, and why he's running for UOSU President."
>
	<section class="about-page">
		<div class="about-header">
			<h1>About Daniel</h1>
			<p class="about-lead">
				Bilingual Software Engineering (CO-OP) student at the University
				of Ottawa with deep experience in student governance, nonprofit
				leadership, campus advocacy, and operational delivery.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- By the Numbers -->
		<div class="highlights-box" aria-label="Experience highlights">
			<h2 class="sr-only">By the Numbers</h2>
			<ul class="highlights-grid" role="list">
				<li class="highlight-item">
					<span class="highlight-stat">UOSU Director & Executive</span
					>
					<span class="highlight-label"
						>Served on both sides of union governance</span
					>
				</li>
				<li class="highlight-item">
					<span class="highlight-stat">Built the Voting Portal</span>
					<span class="highlight-label"
						>Still in use for UOSU elections today</span
					>
				</li>
				<li class="highlight-item">
					<span class="highlight-stat">4 Boards Chaired</span>
					<span class="highlight-label"
						>Across student and nonprofit organizations</span
					>
				</li>
				<li class="highlight-item">
					<span class="highlight-stat">826-Person Hackathon</span>
					<span class="highlight-label"
						>With $95K+ in sponsorship secured</span
					>
				</li>
				<li class="highlight-item">
					<span class="highlight-stat">$400K+ Allocated</span>
					<span class="highlight-label"
						>In engineering student funding decisions</span
					>
				</li>
				<li class="highlight-item">
					<span class="highlight-stat">7 Clubs + ESS + UOSU</span>
					<span class="highlight-label"
						>Unmatched depth of student leadership</span
					>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<!-- UOSU Experience -->
		<article class="about-section" id="uosu">
			<h2>
				<span class="section-icon" aria-hidden="true">🏛️</span>
				UOSU Experience
			</h2>
			<p class="section-intro">
				I've served the Students' Union as both an elected Board
				Director and an Executive Officer — giving me a perspective most
				candidates simply don't have.
			</p>

			<div class="role-card">
				<h3>Communications Commissioner (Executive)</h3>
				<p class="role-period">Nov 2023 – Apr 2024</p>
				<ul class="role-points">
					<li>
						Directed multi-channel communications for 40,000+
						students across social media, newsletters, website, and
						physical outreach
					</li>
					<li>
						Led the 2024 General Elections: introduced in-person
						voting, resolved email delivery issues with University
						IT, and built a real-time turnout tracker
					</li>
					<li>
						Designed and deployed the election voting portal
						(Next.js + Microsoft Entra ID + ElectionBuddy) that's
						still in use today
					</li>
					<li>
						Chaired the hiring of UOSU's first Ombudsperson and
						drafted the Workplace Violence Prevention Policy
					</li>
					<li>
						Authored policy on union advocacy statements and ran
						public consultations and town halls
					</li>
					<li>
						Coordinated with Student Affairs, University IT, and
						Facilities to align communications and operations
					</li>
					<li>
						Conducted accessibility reviews with the Centre for
						Students with Disabilities / Access Service
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<div class="role-card">
				<h3>Information Technology Consultant</h3>
				<p class="role-period">Jun – Aug 2024</p>
				<ul class="role-points">
					<li>
						Administered Microsoft 365 and maintained the UOSU
						website for accurate student-facing information
					</li>
					<li>
						Recruited and onboarded IT and Web staff, including job
						descriptions, interviews, and hiring recommendations
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<div class="role-card">
				<h3>Engineering Director (Elected)</h3>
				<p class="role-period">May – Aug 2023</p>
				<ul class="role-points">
					<li>
						Elected to represent engineering students on the UOSU
						Board of Directors (~40,000 members)
					</li>
					<li>
						Led policy and bylaw reforms adopted by the Board and
						chaired an ad hoc committee
					</li>
					<li>
						Received corporate governance and fiduciary duty
						training from external legal counsel
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</article>

		<!-- Campus Governance -->
		<article class="about-section" id="governance">
			<h2>
				<span class="section-icon" aria-hidden="true">⚖️</span>
				Campus Governance
			</h2>
			<p class="section-intro">
				I've chaired boards, drafted policy, and helped allocate real
				money — the same skills the UOSU President needs every day.
			</p>

			<div class="role-card">
				<h3>VP Internal — Engineering Students' Society</h3>
				<p class="role-period">May – Sep 2025</p>
				<ul class="role-points">
					<li>
						Oversaw governance and compliance of ESS
						sub-associations
					</li>
					<li>
						Advocated to Faculty leadership on student issues
						including space, student experience, and institutional
						decision-making
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<div class="role-card">
				<h3>Chair of the Board — Engineering Students' Society</h3>
				<p class="role-period">May 2024 – Apr 2025</p>
				<ul class="role-points">
					<li>
						Presided over board meetings using Robert's Rules of
						Order, ensuring procedural clarity
					</li>
					<li>
						Led governance modernization — improved meeting process,
						documentation, and compliance expectations
					</li>
					<li>
						Created the Society's first centralized executive
						accountability tracking system
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<div class="role-card">
				<h3>
					Chair of the Board — Canadian Federation of Engineering
					Students
				</h3>
				<p class="role-period">May – Aug 2024</p>
				<ul class="role-points">
					<li>
						Chaired a national board, ensuring compliance with
						organizational policies and governing documents
					</li>
					<li>
						Organized CFES's first Online Seasonal Updates Meeting
						and created bilingual agenda templates
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<div class="role-card">
				<h3>Committee Member — Engineering Endowment Fund</h3>
				<p class="role-period">May 2023 – Winter 2025</p>
				<ul class="role-points">
					<li>
						40+ hours of deliberation evaluating proposals and
						budgets for student engineering initiatives
					</li>
					<li>
						Helped allocate over $400,000 to academic, technical,
						and student-run initiatives
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</article>

		<!-- Community & Nonprofit Leadership -->
		<article class="about-section" id="community">
			<h2>
				<span class="section-icon" aria-hidden="true">🌍</span>
				Community & Nonprofit Leadership
			</h2>

			<div class="role-card">
				<h3>Capital Technology Network / Hack the Hill</h3>
				<p class="role-period">Nov 2022 – Present</p>
				<p class="role-summary">
					Led the incorporation of a youth tech nonprofit. Planned and
					executed Hack the Hill II — 826 participants, 113 projects,
					and over $95,000 in sponsorship. Currently serving as Chair
					of the Board.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="role-card">
				<h3>Board Member — OpenMedia</h3>
				<p class="role-period">Sep 2025 – Present</p>
				<p class="role-summary">
					Governance, financial oversight, and HR for a national
					nonprofit advocating for digital rights, privacy, and an
					open internet.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="role-card">
				<h3>President & Co-Founder — uOttawa Legal Hackers</h3>
				<p class="role-period">Oct 2024 – Present</p>
				<p class="role-summary">
					Founded a student organization at the intersection of law,
					technology, and public policy. Organized events on digital
					rights, AI, and emerging policy issues.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="role-card compact">
				<h3>Writer — Student Affairs, University of Ottawa</h3>
				<p class="role-period">Jan 2026 – Present</p>
				<p class="role-summary">
					Contributes to the uOttawa student newsletter and maintains
					student-facing web content on Drupal.
				</p>
			</div>
		</article>

		<!-- Education -->
		<article class="about-section" id="education">
			<h2>
				<span class="section-icon" aria-hidden="true">🎓</span>
				Education
			</h2>
			<div class="role-card">
				<h3>University of Ottawa</h3>
				<p class="role-period">Sep 2022 – Apr 2027 (expected)</p>
				<p class="role-summary">
					Bachelor of Applied Science, Software Engineering (CO-OP).
					Bilingual (English/French).
				</p>
			</div>
		</article>

		<!-- CTA -->
		<div class="about-cta">
			<a href="/platform/" class="btn btn-primary">Read the Platform →</a>
			<a href="/vote/" class="btn btn-secondary">How to Vote →</a>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>

<style>
	.about-page {
		max-width: var(--content-max);
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: var(--space-8) var(--space-5) var(--space-9);
	}

	.about-header {
		margin-bottom: var(--space-7);
	}

	.about-header h1 {
		margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
	}

	.about-lead {
		font-size: 1.125rem;
		color: var(--color-muted);
		max-width: 56ch;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	/* ── Highlights box ── */
	.highlights-box {
		margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
		padding: var(--space-5);
		background: var(--color-accent-soft);
		border: 1px solid var(--color-accent);
		border-radius: var(--radius-2);
	}

	.sr-only {
		position: absolute;
		width: 1px;
		height: 1px;
		padding: 0;
		margin: -1px;
		overflow: hidden;
		clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0);
		white-space: nowrap;
		border-width: 0;
	}

	.highlights-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(min(100%, 220px), 1fr));
		gap: var(--space-4);
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.highlight-item {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: var(--space-1);
	}

	.highlight-stat {
		font-weight: 700;
		font-size: 1rem;
		color: var(--color-text);
	}

	.highlight-label {
		font-size: 0.8125rem;
		color: var(--color-muted);
		line-height: 1.4;
	}

	/* ── About sections ── */
	.about-section {
		margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
		padding-bottom: var(--space-7);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
	}

	.about-section:last-of-type {
		border-bottom: none;
	}

	.about-section h2 {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: var(--space-3);
		margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
	}

	.section-icon {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
	}

	.section-intro {
		font-size: 1rem;
		color: var(--color-muted);
		line-height: 1.65;
		max-width: 60ch;
		margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
	}

	/* ── Role cards ── */
	.role-card {
		margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
		padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-5);
		background: var(--color-surface);
		border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
		border-radius: var(--radius-2);
	}

	.role-card:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.role-card h3 {
		font-size: 1.0625rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
	}

	.role-period {
		font-size: 0.8125rem;
		color: var(--color-muted);
		margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
	}

	.role-summary {
		font-size: 0.9375rem;
		color: var(--color-muted);
		line-height: 1.65;
		max-width: 60ch;
	}

	.role-points {
		padding-left: var(--space-5);
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: var(--space-2);
	}

	.role-points li {
		font-size: 0.9375rem;
		line-height: 1.65;
		color: var(--color-text);
		max-width: 60ch;
	}

	.role-points li::marker {
		color: var(--color-accent);
	}

	/* ── CTA ── */
	.about-cta {
		display: flex;
		gap: var(--space-3);
		justify-content: center;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		padding-top: var(--space-6);
	}

	.btn {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-5);
		font-size: 0.9375rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		border-radius: var(--radius-1);
		text-decoration: none;
		transition:
			background var(--dur-fast) var(--ease-out),
			color var(--dur-fast) var(--ease-out);
	}

	.btn:hover {
		text-decoration: none;
	}

	.btn-primary {
		background: var(--color-accent);
		color: #fff;
	}

	.btn-primary:hover {
		background: var(--color-accent-hover);
		color: #fff;
	}

	.btn-secondary {
		background: var(--color-surface);
		color: var(--color-text);
		border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
	}

	.btn-secondary:hover {
		border-color: var(--color-muted);
		color: var(--color-text);
	}

	@media (max-width: 640px) {
		.about-page {
			padding: var(--space-6) var(--space-4) var(--space-7);
		}

		.role-card {
			padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
		}
	}
</style>
